                            <comment id="405677" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 28 Feb 2024 22:09:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Migeljan Imeri &amp;lt;mimeri@lanl.gov&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54211&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/54211&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17568&quot; title=&quot;Record full path with RMDIR changelogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17568&quot;&gt;LU-17568&lt;/a&gt; mdt: Append full path to RMDIR changelog record types&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 9f4b9ce772fe72b8a47c961e4ed35f8192148028&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="404749" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 06:21:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the parent directories have been deleted, then there should also be Changelog RMDIR records for those directories later in the logs that can be used to reconstruct the full pathname. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For most use cases the pathname of the deleted files/dirs is not critical to preserve, but it should be possible with the information available. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
